---
// Format A Applied: Abstract → Highlights → Research Questions
---

<section id="problem-statement" class="content-section">
  <div class="section-container">

    <!-- Title -->
    <h2 class="section-heading">
      Sensor-to-Decision Bottleneck in Agentic Autonomy
    </h2>

    <!-- 🔥 NEW: Highlighted Intro Box -->
    <div class="intro-box">
      <p>
        Agentic AI robots increasingly couple high-rate multimodal sensing with learned perception and foundation-model reasoning, yet deployment failures arise from a <strong>sensor-to-decision bottleneck</strong>, not weak models.
        Even with high per-frame accuracy, decisions fail when not grounded in <strong>fresh, decision-time evidence</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 🔥 Key Problems -->
    <div class="problem-highlights">
      <p class="highlight-title">Key System-Level Limitations</p>

      <div class="highlight-box">

        <!-- Item 1 -->
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <div class="highlight-icon">1</div>
          <div class="highlight-content">
            <h4>Stale Decision Inputs</h4>
            <p>Queueing delays force decisions on outdated sensor evidence despite high model accuracy.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Item 2 -->
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <div class="highlight-icon">2</div>
          <div class="highlight-content">
            <h4>Low-Value Data Overload</h4>
            <p>Redundant and vibration-amplified streams saturate onboard pipelines and waste compute.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Item 3 -->
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <div class="highlight-icon">3</div>
          <div class="highlight-content">
            <h4>Delayed Informative Evidence</h4>
            <p>High-value frames arrive too late, degrading real-time decision reliability.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 🔥 Bridge -->
    <div class="bridge-text">
      <p>
        <strong>SenseGuard</strong> addresses this gap by treating robustness as a 
        <strong>decision-time freshness objective</strong>, combining adaptive filtering with model-centric data curation.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<section id="research-questions" class="content-section">
  <div class="section-container">

    <h2 class="section-heading">Research Questions</h2>

    <div class="research-questions-box">

      <!-- RQ1 -->
      <div class="question-item">
        <div class="question-badge">1</div>
        <div class="question-content">
          <h4>Online Autonomy</h4>
          <p>
            How can we maximize <strong>decision-time data freshness</strong> so fast onboard models remain effective under <strong>limited compute</strong>?
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- RQ2 -->
      <div class="question-item">
        <div class="question-badge">2</div>
        <div class="question-content">
          <h4>Offline Improvement</h4>
          <p>
            What <strong>minimal yet sufficient multimodal data</strong> should be retained to accelerate <strong>model improvement</strong> and robustness?
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>

/* ===== INTRO BOX ===== */
.intro-box {
  padding: 1.5rem 1.6rem;
  border-radius: 12px;

  background: linear-gradient(
    135deg,
    rgba(192,94,60,0.06),
    rgba(34,50,83,0.03)
  );

  border: 1px solid rgba(192,94,60,0.1);
  margin-bottom: 2rem;

  transition: all 0.25s ease;
}

.intro-box:hover {
  transform: translateY(-2px);
  box-shadow: 0 8px 22px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
}

.intro-box p {
  margin: 0;
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  line-height: 1.85;
  text-align: justify;
}

.intro-box strong {
  color: #c05e3c;
}

/* ===== TITLE FOR HIGHLIGHTS ===== */
.highlight-title {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: #666;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.4px;
}

/* ===== HIGHLIGHT CARD ===== */
